array.descriptor: Not one more. We cannot allow one more child to be shot at school. We cannot allow one more teacher to make a choice to jump in front of an assault rifle to save the lives of students. We cannot allow one more family to wait for a call or text that never comes. Our children and teachers are dying. We must make it our top priority to save these lives. Come out and join us to make a difference. We will no longer sit and wait for someone else to take action to stop the epidemic of mass shootings!
array.name: March for Our lives

array.descriptor: AIDS has been a major issue in healthcare, especially with those who don't have the proper resources or education. Come out and show your support for expanding government spending in deteriorating AIDS
array.name: AIDS Rally

array.descriptor: The mission of Womens March is to harness the political power of diverse women and their communities to create transformative social change. Come out and be the difference. Empower women. And make a statement for equality!
array.name: Women's March NYC

array.descriptor: School shootings have gotten out of hand. We, as students, should be able to go to school without worrying about guns and being shot. Come join us and make a difference in your community by walking out on April 12th!
array.name: National High School Walkout

array.descriptor: Global warming is getting worse and worse, especially with the continuous use of non-renewable sources of energy. Stand up and march for a greener future for yourself and the next generation!
array.name: People's Climate March

array.descriptor: Come out and show your support for gun control. Mass shootings have gotten worse and worse. Come out and speak for universal background checks and legislative change!
array.name: March for Gun Control

array.descriptor: March on behalf of science. Be the future and join the movement to a more scientific and innovative world!
array.name: March for Science

array.descriptor: Come out and support LGBTQ+ rights in New York!
array.location: 110 St Marks Pl, NY, New York, 10009
array.name: National Pride March
